law.text:
To apply for a license to practice registered nursing or licensed practical nursing, an applicant shall:
Submit to a criminal history records check in accordance with § 8-303 of this subtitle;
Submit to the Board:
An application on the form that the Board requires, including a current address;
Written, verified evidence that the requirement of item (1) of this subsection is being met or has been met;
Written, verified evidence of completion of the appropriate education requirements of § 8-302 of this subtitle; and
Written, verified evidence satisfactory to the Board that the applicant's primary state of residence is Maryland or a state that is not a party state to the Nurse Multistate Licensure Compact set forth in Subtitle 7A of this title; and
Pay to the Board the application fee set by the Board.
